The Very Best of Latin Jazz CD 1 of 2
Audio CD: 25 Jun 2007

Bitrate: 320 kbps

What a cool collection. Some great well known tracks along with some rare grooves. Where did they find that track 'El Sol' by Nuala. Fantastic! No need to listen to anything else this summer! ~ Ricardo Fandango

This is an awesome compilation - absolutely perfect for the summer months. With some real Latin Jazz classics - including the brilliant Mas Que Nada, this 2 CD album is absolutely great from beginning to end. The summer starts here! 

The Very Best of Latin Jazz is the feel good soundtrack to your summer, two CDs packed full of summer sizzlers, perfect for any party or BBQ. Tracks include Mas Que Nada (Black Eyed Peas version), Mambo No. 5, La Bamba, Crickets Sing Anamaria, Soul Bossa Nova (Austin Powers theme) and Many More. Kick start your summer with The Very Best of Latin Jazz. ~ Fiona W
